Advertising Analysis

Defining the Question

A Kenyan entrepreneur has created an online cryptography course and would want to advertise it on her blog. She currently targets audiences originating from various countries. In the past, she ran ads to advertise a related course on the same blog and collected data in the process. She would now like to employ your services as a Data Science Consultant to help her identify which individuals are most likely to click on her ads.

a)Specifying the Question

  1. Identify which Individuals are most likely to click on the clients Ads

b)The metric of Success

Identify which Individuals are most likely to click on the ads based on the data acquired

c)The Context

Online marketing of a Cryptography Class by using Ads

d)Experimental Design

  1. Load Data
  2. Check the Data
  3. Tidy the Data
  4. Analyze the Data

# Mode
getMode <- function(v){
  uniqv <- unique(v)
  uniqv[which.max(tabulate(match(v, uniqv)))]
}

# Only one occurrence of every topic line

From the Male column, 0 means Female and 1 means Male, we have more Females than Males In the Clicked on Ad column, number of clicked versus not clicked are equal

The most popular countries are Afghanistan, Australia, Albania, Bahamas are the top 4 countries The most popular age is 31 years Females spend more time in the Internet compared to Males and with more Females spending time on the Internet, we see that most of them click on Ads compared to Males

But there is still a significant number of Females who dont click on Ads.

The Countries that had the highest number in clicked ads was Australia, Afghanistan and Bahamas

The Ad Topic Line are there is only one occurrence of each.

Correlation

# Correlation Matrix
correlation_matrix = cor(numeric_col)
View(round(correlation_matrix,2))

Clicked on Ad column has strong negative correlation with Daily Time Spent on Internet and Daily Internet Usage It has a moderate negative Correlation with Area Income and a Moderate Positive Correlation with Age

Therefore this columns 1.Daily Time Spent on Internet 2.Daily Internet Usage 3.Area Income 4.Age Can we used to determine if a an Ad will be clicked on or not

Conclusion

The Client could concentrate on the between 35-40 age group and mostly Female users.

The client could add content on the blog that attract more Male Users because the more time spent on the blog the higher the Area Income.

The Ads as well should be attractive to the Male the users so that they will click on the Ads more
